100 SCENARIOS 1) Create a simple message on TypeScript
var message:string = &ldquo;Hello World&rdquo; console.log(message)
On compiling, it will generate following JavaScript code.
//Generated by typescript 1.8.10 var message = &ldquo;Hello World&rdquo;; console.log(message);
2) Run/Compile
tsc Test.ts node Test.js
3) Multiple files can be run at once
Example : tsc file1.ts, file2.ts, file3.ts
4) TypeScript is Case-sensitive
console.log(&ldquo;hello world&rdquo;) console.log(&ldquo;We are learning TypeScript&rdquo;
